  "unmapped_findings": [
    "B2 intermetallic is non-shearable, which provides higher precipitation strengthening than κ-carbide that is sheared by dislocations",
    "B2 stringer bands delay recrystallization of γ phase similar to carbide/nitride precipitates",
    "High-speed hot rolling reduces B2 stringer band fraction from 16% to 11%, allowing more γ phase to absorb plastic strain and delay crack propagation",
    "The alloy is suitable for automotive body in white application, 10% density reduction can reduce total vehicle mass by ~6%, bringing significant economic and environmental benefits"
  ]
